        <h1>LeetCode 1437: Check If All 1's Are at Least Length K Places Away (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given an binary array nums and an integer k, return true if all 1's are at least k places away from each
                other, otherwise return false. Two 1's at indices i and j are k places away if abs(i - j) >= k + 1,
                meaning
                there are at least k elements between them.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,0,0,0,1,0,0,1], k = 2 → Output: true. Each pair of consecutive 1's has at least 2 zeros
                between them.
                Input: nums = [1,0,0,1,0,1], k = 2 → Output: false. The second and third 1's are only 1 position apart.
                Input: nums = [1,1,1,1,1], k = 0 → Output: true. Since k = 0, consecutive 1's are allowed.
                Input: nums = [0,1,0,1], k = 1 → Output: true. The two 1's are exactly k+1 = 2 positions apart.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool kLengthApart(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums, int k) {
        if (k == 0) 
            return true;  // No gap needed
        
        int n = nums.size();
        int c = 0;  // current pointer
        int nx = 1; // next pointer
        while (c &lt; n &amp;&amp; nx &lt; n) {
            if (nums[nx] == 1) {       // found next 1
                if (nums[c] == 1 &amp;&amp; nx - c &lt;= k)
                    return false;     // gap too small
                c = nx;               // shift current to this 1
            }
            nx++;                     // keep moving next pointer
        }
        return true;
    }
};</code></pre>
